The paper deals with graph partitioning problems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of graph theory and combinatorial optimization techniques also suggests the categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) and game theory (cs.GT) as possible sub-fields.
